p:
We reclassified predicted habitat using a 0.25 threshold interval to label three habitat suitability classes: low suitability habitat when occurrence probability ranged between 25% and 50%; suitable habitat if occurrence probability was in the 50–75% interval; and high suitability habitat if occurrence probability was over 75%, values below 25% were considered as inappropriate habitat (
 Hu & Jiang, 2012; 
 González et al., 2013; 
 Shrestha & Bawa, 2014).
